Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> watch

Purpose:
  Follow durable events and progress for one queue job.

Usage:
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> watch [--jsonl] [--from beginning|now]

Arguments:
  <job-id>              Full job id or an unambiguous prefix.

Options:
  --jsonl               Print one JSON event per line. Recommended for agents.
  --from beginning      Replay stored history, then follow new events. Default.
  --from now            Follow only new events.

Progress:
  - Human output shows lifecycle events as lines and the current status as a refreshed status line.
  - JSONL `status_snapshot` events expose `step`, `phase`, `counters`, and `tokens` when available.
  - Status refreshes are throttled when the phase does not change.

Examples:
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/75d12f7e watch
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/75d12f7e watch --jsonl --from beginning
